Log a warning when `target.delete()` returns false and the file still exists:
```kotlin
} catch (t: Throwable) {
  if (target.exists() && !target.delete()) {
    errorLog.e("attachment-save",
      "failed to clean partial attachment: ${target.absolutePath}")
  }
  throw t
}
```
Note: `errorLog.e` is suspending; either make `writeAttachmentPayload` `suspend` or buffer the cleanup failure and log it from the outer `suspend` function.
